(17, 'Radiology', 'MRI 3 Tesla', 'Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) scanners that function at a magnetic field strength of 3 Tesla are known as MRI 3 Tesla scanners.', '486611016_MRI 3 Tesla.png', 'MRI 3 Tesla', '<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>What is MRI 3 Tesla?</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) scanners that function at a magnetic field strength of 3 Tesla are known as MRI 3 Tesla scanners. High-resolution images of the inside parts of the body are provided by it, which makes it perfect for precise diagnostic imaging.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Type of MRI 3 Tesla:</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Subtypes: 3T MRI scanners can be open or closed (bore) systems.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Benefits of MRI 3 Tesla:</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">High Resolution: Provides clearer and more detailed images than lower-strength MRI machines.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Faster Scanning: Reduces scan time, making it more comfortable for patients.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Better Diagnostic Accuracy: Enhances the ability to diagnose complex conditions, particularly in the brain and musculoskeletal system.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">At our Delhi MRI Centre, we are dedicated to providing the highest quality diagnostic services with state-of-the-art technology and exceptional patient care. Here&rsquo;s why you should choose us:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Advanced Technology: </strong></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">We use the latest 3 Tesla MRI machines, ensuring the most accurate and detailed imaging possible.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Experienced Staff: </strong></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Our team of radiologists and technicians are highly trained and experienced, guaranteeing professional and precise diagnostic services.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Comprehensive Services: </strong></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">We offer a wide range of diagnostic tests, including CT scans, ultrasounds, digital X-rays, and more, all under one roof.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Patient-Centered Care: </strong></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">We prioritize your comfort and convenience, providing a welcoming environment and efficient service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Trusted Reputation:</strong></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"> Recognized as one of the best diagnostic centers in South Delhi, we are committed to excellence and patient satisfaction.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">What makes the 3 Tesla MRI different from other MRI machines?</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">The 3 Tesla MRI operates at a higher magnetic field strength, which provides clearer and more detailed images compared to lower-strength MRI machines. This allows for better diagnostic accuracy, particularly for complex conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">What should I expect during my MRI scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">During an MRI scan, you will lie on a table that slides into the MRI machine. The procedure is non-invasive and painless. You may hear some loud noises during the scan, but ear protection will be provided for your comfort.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">How do I prepare for my MRI scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Generally, no special preparation is needed for an MRI scan. However, you should inform your doctor or technician if you have any metal implants, pacemakers, or are pregnant. You may be asked to remove any metallic items such as jewellery before the scan.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Are there any risks associated with MRI scans?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">MRI scans are very safe and do not use ionising radiation. However, the strong magnetic field can affect electronic devices and implants. It&#39;s important to inform your doctor of any medical devices you have before the scan.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">How soon will I receive my MRI results?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Your MRI results will typically be ready within a few days. Our radiologists will analyse the images and provide a detailed report to your referring physician, who will then discuss the results with you.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'mritesla', 'What is MRI 3 Tesla?', 'Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) scanners that function at a magnetic field strength of 3 Tesla are known as MRI 3 Tesla scanners.', 'MRI 3 Tesla', 1),
(18, 'Radiology', 'CT Scan', 'A CT Scan, or Computed Tomography scan, is a diagnostic imaging procedure that uses a combination of X-rays and computer technology to create detailed cross-sectional images of the body.', '806101865_CT Scan.png', 'CT Scan', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>CT Scan</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is a CT Scan?</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">A CT Scan, or Computed Tomography scan, is a diagnostic imaging procedure that uses a combination of X-rays and computer technology to create detailed cross-sectional images of the body. This allows doctors to examine bones, organs, and tissues with high precision.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Types of CT Scans:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Standard CT: The most common type, used for general diagnostic purposes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Helical CT: Also known as spiral CT, it uses continuous scanning to create more detailed images.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Multi-slice CT: Captures multiple slices simultaneously, offering even more detailed images and faster scan times.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Benefits of a CT Scan:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Detailed Images: Provides high-resolution images of bones, organs, and tissues.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Quick and Painless: The procedure is fast, typically taking only a few minutes, and is non-invasive.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Versatile: Capable of detecting a wide range of conditions, from bone fractures to cancers.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Our Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering state-of-the-art CT scan services. We pride ourselves on providing top-notch diagnostic imaging with expert radiologists and the latest technology. Our commitment to patient care and accuracy makes us the preferred choice for many.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">What should I expect during a CT scan?</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">During a CT scan, you will lie on a table that slides into a large, doughnut-shaped machine. The procedure is painless and typically takes about 5&nbsp;minutes. You may be asked to hold your breath briefly while images are taken.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is a CT scan safe?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, CT scans are generally safe. They use a low dose of radiation, and the benefits of accurate diagnosis usually outweigh the risks. However, inform your doctor if you are pregnant or have any allergies, especially to contrast materials.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to prepare for a CT scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Preparation depends on the type of CT scan. You may need to avoid eating or drinking for a few hours before the scan, especially if contrast dye is used. Your doctor will provide specific instructions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How quickly will I receive my results?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Results are typically available within 5-6&nbsp;hours. Our radiologists will analyze the images and send a detailed report to your referring physician, who will discuss the findings with you.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can I go back to normal activities after a CT scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, you can usually resume your normal activities immediately after the scan. If contrast dye was used, you might be advised to drink plenty of fluids to help flush it out of your system.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'ctscan', 'What is a CT Scan?', 'What is a CT Scan?', 'What is a CT Scan?', 1),
(19, 'Radiology', 'Clinical Pathology Collection Centre', 'Clinical Pathology Collection Centre: A facility where blood, urine, and other body fluid samples are collected for laboratory analysis.', '789044292_Clinical Pathology.png', 'Clinical Pathology Collection Centre', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Clinical Pathology Collection Centre</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Clinical Pathology Collection Centre: A facility where blood, urine, and other body fluid samples are collected for laboratory analysis.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Types of Clinical Pathology Collection Centre:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Medical service facility.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes general pathology, hematology, biochemistry, and microbiology.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Benefits of Clinical Pathology Collection Centre:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Convenient Sample Collection: Central location for sample collection.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Comprehensive Testing: Offers a wide range of laboratory tests.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Accurate Diagnosis: Provides critical information for diagnosing medical conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">At Delhi MRI Centre, we are recognized as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi. Our state-of-the-art facility in Hauz Khas is equipped with advanced diagnostic technology and staffed by experienced professionals. We are committed to providing accurate and timely results to ensure the best possible care for our patients.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">What types of tests are available at the Clinical Pathology Collection Centre?</span></span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Our centre offers a wide range of tests, including general pathology, hematology, biochemistry, and microbiology. This ensures comprehensive diagnostic capabilities for various medical conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How do I prepare for a pathology test?</span></span></span></strong>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Preparation varies depending on the specific test. Some tests may require fasting or special instructions, which will be provided to you when you schedule your appointment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How quickly will I receive my test results?</span></span></span></strong>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Test results are typically available within 24&nbsp;hours. Our team ensures timely processing and reporting of your results to your healthcare provider.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Are the tests at Delhi MRI Centre safe and reliable?</span></span></span></strong>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, all tests are conducted using advanced technology and adhere to strict quality control protocols to ensure safety and reliability. Our laboratory is staffed by experienced professionals dedicated to accurate diagnostics.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can I book an appointment for a pathology test online?</span></span></span></strong>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, you can conveniently book an appointment through our website or by calling our centre. We offer flexible scheduling to accommodate your needs.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'clinical_pathology', 'best Clinical Pathology Collection Centre in south delhi', 'Clinical Pathology Collection Centre: A facility where blood, urine, and other body fluid samples are collected for laboratory analysis.', 'Clinical Pathology Collection Centre , Best clinical pathology in south delhi', 1),
(20, 'Radiology', 'DEXA Bone Densitometry', 'DEXA (Dual-Energy X-ray Absorptiometry) Bone Densitometry: A test that measures bone density to assess the risk of osteoporosis.', '361028028_DEXA Bone Densitometry.png', 'DEXA Bone Densitometry', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is DEXA Bone Densitometry?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">DEXA (Dual-Energy X-ray Absorptiometry) Bone Densitometry: A test that measures bone density to assess the risk of osteoporosis.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Type of DEXA Bone Densitometry:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes central DEXA (spine and hip) and peripheral DEXA (wrist, heel).</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Benefits of DEXA Bone Densitometry:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Accurate Measurement: Provides precise bone density readings.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Early Detection: Identifies osteoporosis and fracture risk early.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Guides Treatment: Helps monitor the effectiveness of osteoporosis treatments.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">At Delhi MRI Centre, we take pride in being recognized as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi. Our commitment to excellence extends to our DEXA Bone Densitometry services, providing accurate assessments of bone health and personalized treatment guidance.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How often should I undergo DEXA Bone Densitometry testing?</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The frequency of testing depends on various factors, including age, gender, and medical history. Your healthcare provider can recommend the appropriate interval for screening based on your individual risk factors.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is DEXA Bone Densitometry safe?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, DEXA Bone Densitometry is a safe and non-invasive procedure that uses minimal radiation exposure. It is widely regarded as the gold standard for assessing bone density and osteoporosis risk.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">What can I expect during a DEXA Bone Densitometry scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">During the scan, you will lie comfortably on a table while a scanner passes over the areas being examined, typically the spine, hip, or wrist. The procedure is painless and takes only a few minutes to complete.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can DEXA Bone Densitometry detect other bone conditions besides osteoporosis?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">While DEXA primarily assesses bone density and osteoporosis risk, it can also provide valuable information about other bone conditions such as osteopenia and bone loss due to certain medical treatments or conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How can I interpret the results of my DEXA Bone Densitometry scan?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Your healthcare provider will interpret the results of your DEXA scan and discuss them with you in detail. They will explain your bone density measurements and what they mean for your bone health, as well as recommend any necessary follow-up or treatment options.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'DEXA Bone Densitometry', 'DEXA Bone Densitometry', 'DEXA (Dual-Energy X-ray Absorptiometry) Bone Densitometry: A test that measures bone density to assess the risk of osteoporosis.', 'DEXA Bone Densitometry', 1),
(21, 'Cardiology', 'Echo Cardiography', 'Echo Cardiography: A test that uses ultrasound waves to produce images of the heart, assessing its structure and function.', '750848270_Echo Cardiography.png', 'Echo Cardiography', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is Echo Cardiography?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Echo Cardiography: A test that uses ultrasound waves to produce images of the heart, assessing its structure and function.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Type of Echo Cardiography:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes transthoracic echocardiogram, transesophageal echocardiogram, and stress echocardiogram.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Benefits of Echo Cardiography:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive: Safe and painless procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Detailed Heart Evaluation: Provides comprehensive information about heart size, shape, and function.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Early Detection: Helps detect heart conditions early.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre stands out as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced diagnostic services including Echo Cardiography. Our commitment to excellence and patient care ensures accurate and timely diagnosis of heart conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">What is the difference between transthoracic and transesophageal echocardiogram?</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Transthoracic echocardiogram is performed externally on the chest, while transesophageal echocardiogram involves inserting a probe into the esophagus for a closer view of the heart. Your cardiologist will recommend the appropriate type based on your condition.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is Echo Cardiography safe for all age groups?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, Echo Cardiography is safe for all age groups, from infants to the elderly. It is a non-invasive procedure with no known side effects.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an Echo Cardiography procedure take?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The duration of the procedure varies depending on the type of echocardiogram and the complexity of the evaluation needed. Generally, it takes about 10-15&nbsp;minutes to an hour.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can Echo Cardiography diagnose all heart conditions?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Echo Cardiography is a valuable tool for diagnosing a wide range of heart conditions, including valve abnormalities, heart defects, and heart muscle disorders. However, additional tests may be needed for certain conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to prepare for an Echo Cardiography test?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Preparation requirements may vary depending on the specific type of echocardiogram. Your healthcare provider will provide you with specific instructions, which may include fasting for a few hours before the test.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'echo_cardiography', 'Echo Cardiography', 'Echo Cardiography: A test that uses ultrasound waves to produce images of the heart, assessing its structure and function.', 'Echo Cardiography', 1),
(22, 'Radiology', 'Digital X-Ray', 'Digital X-Ray is an imaging technique that uses digital sensors to capture X-ray images, which are then viewed on a computer.', '520765777_Digital X-Ray.png', 'What is Digital X-Ray?', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is Digital X-Ray?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Digital X-Ray is an imaging technique that uses digital sensors to capture X-ray images, which are then viewed on a computer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Type of Digital X-Ray:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes digital radiography and computed radiography.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Benefits of Digital X-Ray:</strong></span></span></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Immediate Results: Images are available instantly.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Lower Radiation: Often requires less radiation than traditional X-rays.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Enhanced Image Quality: Provides clear and detailed images.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies Colour Doppler and Digital X-Ray. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an Colour Doppler procedure take?</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The duration of the procedure varies depending on the area being examined and the complexity of the assessment. Generally, it takes less than a&nbsp;&nbsp;minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is Colour Doppler safe during pregnancy?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, Colour Doppler are considered safe during pregnancy and are commonly used to monitor fetal development and assess maternal health.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can Digital X-Ray be used for all types of imaging?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Digital X-Ray is suitable for a wide range of imaging needs, including bone fractures, dental imaging, and chest X-rays. However, certain conditions may require other imaging modalities for better visualization.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to make an appointment for Digital X-Ray?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">While walk-in appointments may be available, it is recommended to schedule an appointment to minimize waiting time and ensure prompt service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How soon can I expect to receive my Digital X-Ray results?</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Digital X-Ray images are available instantly and can be viewed by your healthcare provider shortly after the procedure. Your provider will interpret the results and discuss them with you during your follow-up appointment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', 'digital_xray', 'What is Digital X-Ray?', 'Digital X-Ray is an imaging technique that uses digital sensors to capture X-ray images, which are then viewed on a computer.', 'Digital X-Ray', 1),
(23, 'Cardiology', 'ECG (Electrocardiogram)', 'ECG is a diagnostic tool that measures and records the electrical activity of the heart, producing a waveform that is analyzed to detect various heart conditions.', '482093283_ECG.png', 'ECG (Electrocardiogram)', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is ECG?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">ECG is a diagnostic tool that measures and records the electrical activity of the heart, producing a waveform that is analyzed to detect various heart conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type of ECG:</span></span></span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes resting ECG, stress ECG, and Holter monitoring.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Benefits of ECG:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive: A simple and painless procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Quick Results: Provides immediate insights into heart health.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Early Detection: Helps in early diagnosis of heart diseases.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Why Choose Us?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies including ECG. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an ECG procedure take?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The procedure usually takes less then a&nbsp;minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is ECG safe?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, ECG is a safe and non-invasive test.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can ECG detect all heart problems?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">ECG can detect many heart problems, but some conditions may require further testing with other imaging modalities.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to make an appointment for ECG?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">While walk-in appointments may be available, scheduling an appointment is recommended to minimize waiting time and ensure prompt service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How soon can I expect to receive my ECG results?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">ECG results are available immediately and can be reviewed by your healthcare provider shortly after the procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'ecg', 'ECG', 'ECG is a diagnostic tool that measures and records the electrical activity of the heart, producing a waveform that is analyzed to detect various heart conditions.', 'ecg', 1);
INSERT INTO `services` (`id`, `category`, `title`, `short_description`, `image`, `image_alt_tag`, `description`, `url`, `meta_title`, `meta_desc`, `meta_keyword`, `status`) VALUES
(24, 'Neurology', 'EEG (Electroencephalogram)', 'EEG is a diagnostic tool that records electrical activity in the brain, helping to diagnose conditions like epilepsy, sleep disorders, and other neurological conditions.', '357426155_EEG.png', 'EEG (Electroencephalogram)', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is EEG?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>EEG</strong> is a diagnostic tool that records electrical activity in the brain, helping to diagnose conditions like epilepsy, sleep disorders, and other neurological conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type of EEG:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes routine EEG, ambulatory EEG, and video EEG monitoring.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Benefits of EEG:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive: Safe and painless procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Detailed Brain Activity: Provides comprehensive information about brain function.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Diagnostic Precision: Helps in accurate diagnosis of neurological conditions.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Why Choose Us?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies including EEG. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</span></span></span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an EEG procedure take?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The duration varies but typically takes about 20&nbsp;minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is EEG safe?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, EEG is a safe and non-invasive procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can EEG detect all brain disorders?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">EEG is effective for many conditions but may need to be supplemented with other tests for a complete diagnosis.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to make an appointment for EEG?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Scheduling an appointment is recommended to ensure timely service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How soon can I expect to receive my EEG results?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">EEG results are usually available within a few days, depending on the complexity of the analysis.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'eeg', 'EEG', 'EEG is a diagnostic tool that records electrical activity in the brain, helping to diagnose conditions like epilepsy, sleep disorders, and other neurological conditions.', 'EEG', 1),
(25, 'Neurology', 'EMG (Electromyography)', 'EMG is a diagnostic procedure that assesses the health of muscles and the nerve cells that control them by measuring the electrical activity produced by muscles.', '353332489_EMG.png', 'EMG', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>What is EMG?</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">EMG is a diagnostic procedure that assesses the health of muscles and the nerve cells that control them by measuring the electrical activity produced by muscles.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type of EMG:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Type</strong>: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes surface EMG and intramuscular EMG.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Benefits of EMG:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Accurate Diagnosis: Helps in diagnosing muscle and nerve disorders.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive Options: Surface EMG is non-invasive.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Functional Assessment: Evaluates muscle and nerve function.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Why Choose Us?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies including EMG. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an EMG procedure take?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The procedure usually takes about 30 minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is EMG safe?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, EMG is generally safe. There might be slight discomfort during needle insertion in intramuscular EMG.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can EMG diagnose all muscle and nerve conditions?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">EMG is very effective but may need to be used in conjunction with other tests.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to make an appointment for EMG?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">It is recommended to schedule an appointment to ensure prompt service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How soon can I expect to receive my EMG results?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">EMG results are typically available within a few days.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'emg', 'EMG (Electromyography)', 'EMG is a diagnostic procedure that assesses the health of muscles and the nerve cells that control them by measuring the electrical activity produced by muscles.', 'EMG (Electromyography)', 1),
(26, 'Neurology', 'NCS (Nerve Conduction studies)', 'NCS is a diagnostic test that measures the speed at which electrical signals move through a nerve, used to diagnose nerve damage and dysfunction.', '635008158_NCV.png', 'NCS (Nerve Conduction studies)', '<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>What is NCS?</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>NCS</strong> is a diagnostic test that measures the speed at which electrical signals move through a nerve, used to diagnose nerve damage and dysfunction.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Type of NCS:</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\"><strong>Type</strong>: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes sensory nerve conduction studies and motor nerve conduction studies.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Benefits of NCS:</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Accurate Measurement: Provides precise information about nerve function.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive: A minimally invasive procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Early Detection: Helps in early diagnosis of nerve disorders.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Why Choose Us?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies including NCS. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How long does an NCS procedure take?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The procedure usually takes about 30&nbsp;minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Is NCS safe?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, NCS&nbsp;is a safe and minimally invasive test.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Can NCS detect all nerve conditions?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">NCS&nbsp;is effective for many conditions but may need to be supplemented with other tests.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Do I need to make an appointment for NCS?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Scheduling an appointment is recommended to ensure timely service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">How soon can I expect to receive my NCS results?</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">NCS&nbsp;results are typically available within a few days.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'ncs', 'NCS (Nerve Conduction studies)', 'NCS is a diagnostic test that measures the speed at which electrical signals move through a nerve, used to diagnose nerve damage and dysfunction.', 'NCS (Nerve Conduction studies)', 1),
(27, 'Radiology', 'Ultrasound & Colour Doppler', 'Ultrasound is an imaging technique that uses sound waves to create images of internal body structures. Colour Doppler adds color to the images to show the flow of blood within the vessels.', '145766093_ULTRASOUND & COLOUR DOPPLER.png', 'Ultrasound & Colour Doppler', '<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>What is Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler?</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Ultrasound is an imaging technique that uses sound waves to create images of internal body structures. Colour Doppler adds color to the images to show the flow of blood within the vessels.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Type of Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler:</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Type: Diagnostic imaging technology.</span></span></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Subtypes: Includes standard ultrasound, Doppler ultrasound, and 3D/4D ultrasound.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Benefits of Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Non-Invasive: Safe and painless procedure.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Real-Time Imaging: Provides live images of internal organs and blood flow.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Versatile: Used for a wide range of diagnostic purposes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Why Choose Us?</strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Delhi MRI Centre is renowned as the best diagnostic centre in South Delhi, offering advanced imaging technologies like Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler. Our commitment to excellence and patient care sets us apart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#434343\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):</span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Q How long does an Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler procedure take?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">The duration varies but generally takes about 15-30 minutes.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Q Is Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler safe during pregnancy?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Yes, Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler are considered safe during pregnancy and are commonly used to monitor fetal development and assess maternal health.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Q Can Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler be used for all types of imaging?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler are suitable for a wide range of imaging needs, but certain conditions may require other imaging modalities.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Q Do I need to make an appointment for Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">While walk-in appointments may be available, scheduling an appointment is recommended to minimize waiting time and ensure prompt service.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Q1 How soon can I expect to receive my Ultrasound &amp; Colour Doppler results?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">Results are usually available shortly after the procedure and will be discussed by your healthcare provider during your follow-up appointment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'ultrasound_colour', 'best Ultrasound & Colour Doppler in south delhi', 'Ultrasound is an imaging technique that uses sound waves to create images of internal body structures. Colour Doppler adds color to the images to show the flow of blood within the vessels.', 'Ultrasound & Colour Doppler', 1);

